        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 12:27PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 1226 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sumner, or 8 miles northwest of Paris, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Camp Maxey, Powderly, Paris, and Pat Mayse Lake around 1230 PM
CDT.
Arthur City around 1235 PM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Toco, Chicota, Globe,
Brookston, Faught, Tigertown, Forest Chapel, Novice, Belk, and
Midcity.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
